					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Now don't get me wrong, I absolutely love Super Mario Bros. 3, and it's extremely advanced for the NES, but I can't help but feel like it was trying way too hard to do stuff the NES was simply not capable of doing. They tried to have not only horizontal scrolling like in the first  Super Mario, but also have vertical scrolling, which led to them clipping the leftmost 8 pixel area as well as having the annoying incorrect attribute table on the rightmost 8 pixels. (I don't know if it's incorrect attribute tables, but what I'm talking about is the incorrectly colored area when scrolling.) They also tried way too hard to have a lot of palettes on screen, which leads to occasionally miscolored power ups or in the toad house, green fireballs. Of course, this could be just me.</div>

