					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">They just didn't understand the NES that well back in 1987 during development.<br />Every technical problem the game has could be resolved if the game were redeveloped today.  For instance, there's a &gt;16 px black area at the bottom of the screen.  Which means the entire playfield could be rendered on screen using Vertical Mirroring with no attribute clash.<br /><br />You could use a 208px tall playfield, and 32px tall status bar, and four IRQ split points to make the 208px tall playfield wrap within a 192px area, show the status bar, and hide the bottom 16px.</div>

					
